1
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,074
Delicious Vegan Sausages, Cheese
and Burgers - Vegusto.co.uk

2
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:02,568
You might need that.

3
00:01:03,235 --> 00:01:04,236
Where'd you find this?

4
00:01:04,803 --> 00:01:07,739
It was in one of those cartons.

5
00:01:11,509 --> 00:01:12,310
Needs oil.

6
00:01:12,710 --> 00:01:13,711
Who doesn't?

7
00:01:15,980 --> 00:01:16,714
You ready?

8
00:01:18,582 --> 00:01:19,950
- I'm not going.
- Mom!

9
00:01:20,851 --> 00:01:22,820
I've got two children,
I don't need a third.

10
00:01:23,554 --> 00:01:25,255
Why is it so important that I go?

11
00:01:25,989 --> 00:01:28,591
For one thing, it'd be nice if you
just left the room.

12
00:01:29,526 --> 00:01:31,494
Besides, these are your old friends.

13
00:01:34,063 --> 00:01:35,564
They probably won't remember me.

14
00:01:36,932 --> 00:01:38,701
The "Queen of Diamonds," Dottie Hinson?

15
00:01:39,435 --> 00:01:41,270
Margaret, it just isn't a good idea.

16
00:01:42,004 --> 00:01:44,873
Come on, Mom.
You'll get to see Aunt Kit.

17
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,942
- You never see each other.
- We still won't.

18
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:50,978
She'll be traveling around
with that husband of hers.

19
00:01:51,846 --> 00:01:53,481
Frank. He has a name.

20
00:01:54,181 --> 00:01:55,816
He's always been very nice to you.

21
00:01:56,951 --> 00:01:58,318
He makes me nervous.

22
00:01:59,386 --> 00:02:01,788
There's a lot of reasons
why I can't go.

23
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:03,990
Honey...

24
00:02:05,025 --> 00:02:08,027
...I'm not comfortable about this.
I'm not really part of it.

25
00:02:09,429 --> 00:02:11,964
It was never that important.
It was just something I did.

26
00:02:12,898 --> 00:02:16,402
When will you realize how special it
was, how much it all meant?

27
00:02:19,971 --> 00:02:22,374
I know how you feel. I really do.

28
00:02:24,075 --> 00:02:25,343
But you're going.

29
00:02:30,214 --> 00:02:31,315
Car.

30
00:02:33,851 --> 00:02:36,320
- Car, train, bus. I'm tired already.
- Sleep on the plane.

31
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,688
Grandma's out.
Is there a fire?

32
00:02:39,389 --> 00:02:40,123
Wisenheimer.

33
00:02:40,523 --> 00:02:42,992
Julie's watching you.
I don't want any bad reports.

34
00:02:44,794 --> 00:02:45,728
- Bye, Grandma.
- Bye.

35
00:02:46,696 --> 00:02:48,197
Jeffrey, come here.

36
00:02:51,967 --> 00:02:54,636
No matter what your brother does,
he's littler than you.

37
00:02:55,570 --> 00:02:57,672
Give him a chance to shoot. Promise?

38
00:03:00,075 --> 00:03:01,576
Bobby, come here.

39
00:03:03,711 --> 00:03:04,712
Kill him.

40
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:07,548
Come on, you'll miss your plane.

41
00:03:33,405 --> 00:03:35,307
I still think I shouldn't go.

42
00:04:49,941 --> 00:04:51,009
Get a hit, Beans!

43
00:05:02,386 --> 00:05:04,521
I'm coming, Mae! I'm coming!

44
00:05:14,864 --> 00:05:17,266
This week in the world of sports.

45
00:05:18,667 --> 00:05:20,769
With the boys overseas
and off to war...

46
00:05:21,536 --> 00:05:23,672
...baseball pitches in
for the war effort.

47
00:05:24,806 --> 00:05:26,641
Trading bats for bullets,
Yankee Joe DiMaggio...

48
00:05:27,342 --> 00:05:29,177
...promises to give
those Nazis a jolt.

49
00:05:30,344 --> 00:05:32,313
Ace fireballer Bob Feller...

50
00:05:33,047 --> 00:05:35,382
...has traded Cleveland gray
for Navy blue.

51
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:38,118
Baseball's biggest stars say...

52
00:05:38,852 --> 00:05:41,154
..."Look out, Mr. Hitler.
The Yanks are coming. "

53
00:05:41,955 --> 00:05:44,357
Not to mention the Indians,
Red Sox and Tigers.

54
00:05:45,225 --> 00:05:47,760
And they won't come back
till it's over, over there.

55
00:05:50,496 --> 00:05:54,133
Meanwhile, Chicago club owner
Walter Harvey, the candy-bar king...

56
00:05:55,334 --> 00:05:58,703
...met with other team owners at
the Harvey Mansion as rumours persist...

57
00:05:59,838 --> 00:06:03,141
...that baseball may be shut down
for the duration of the war.

58
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:07,011
Harvey's promotional whiz kid,
Ira Lowenstein...

59
00:06:08,012 --> 00:06:11,382
...has been given the job of
figuring out how to keep baseball going.

60
00:06:12,649 --> 00:06:14,551
Good luck, Mr. Lowenstein.

61
00:06:23,893 --> 00:06:25,261
Strike 2!

62
00:06:35,670 --> 00:06:36,905
Hey, fatso!

63
00:06:37,405 --> 00:06:39,874
Get the hell out of the way!
What are you, crazy?

64
00:06:41,843 --> 00:06:43,211
Strike 3!

65
00:06:48,048 --> 00:06:49,049
Kit!

66
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:52,919
- Sis, don't swing at her high pitch.
- I can hit it.

67
00:06:53,820 --> 00:06:55,655
- You can't.
- I can.

68
00:06:56,356 --> 00:06:58,391
This bat's too heavy.
You'll never get it around.

69
00:06:59,158 --> 00:07:00,259
I will!

70
00:07:01,394 --> 00:07:04,330
Listen. There's a big hole
on the right side. Don't look.

71
00:07:05,264 --> 00:07:07,299
- Unless she pitches inside, pull it.
- I know.

72
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:09,001
Batter up!

73
00:07:11,103 --> 00:07:12,103
No high ones.

74
00:07:12,671 --> 00:07:13,872
I like the high ones!

75
00:07:14,372 --> 00:07:16,074
- Mule!
- Nag!

76
00:07:24,581 --> 00:07:27,184
Come on, Kit.
Keep your eye on the ball.

77
00:07:32,789 --> 00:07:34,057
Strike 1!

78
00:07:45,033 --> 00:07:46,134
Strike 2!

79
00:07:47,636 --> 00:07:48,503
Too high.

80
00:07:55,610 --> 00:07:56,978
All right, Kit. Look it over!

81
00:07:57,578 --> 00:07:59,146
Look it over there!

82
00:08:00,047 --> 00:08:01,482
Strike 3!

83
00:08:08,388 --> 00:08:10,523
All right, 2 outs, everybody.
Two away!

84
00:08:11,257 --> 00:08:13,025
Better luck next time!

85
00:08:13,926 --> 00:08:15,828
Knock it out of here! Okay, Dottie!

86
00:08:18,030 --> 00:08:19,131
Batter up!

87
00:08:27,272 --> 00:08:28,439
Right in here!

88
00:08:33,077 --> 00:08:34,578
Bring them in there, Dottie!

89
00:08:37,715 --> 00:08:38,582
Ball!

90
00:08:45,488 --> 00:08:47,390
Keep your eye on it, Dottie!

91
00:08:48,224 --> 00:08:50,393
One hit and we win!

92
00:09:01,169 --> 00:09:03,071
That's it, Dottie! You did it!

93
00:09:06,074 --> 00:09:07,375
That's the ball game!

94
00:09:18,985 --> 00:09:21,354
Hey, Kit! What are you swinging
those high ones for?

95
00:09:22,155 --> 00:09:24,290
Good thing your sister bailed you out.

96
00:09:25,925 --> 00:09:28,094
How about the two bucks you owe me
for this game?

97
00:09:28,828 --> 00:09:31,096
Kit! Wait up, I'll give you a ride!

98
00:09:34,299 --> 00:09:35,434
Stop kicking the rocks.

99
00:09:35,934 --> 00:09:36,868
I'm sorry.

100
00:09:37,636 --> 00:09:40,705
- That game just made me so mad.
- We won. Get mad if we lose.

101
00:09:41,706 --> 00:09:43,674
That last pitch was
right down the middle.

102
00:09:44,609 --> 00:09:46,644
If I'd have swung at that,
I'd be the hero.

103
00:09:47,445 --> 00:09:50,047
- You got me so crazy-
- I only said lay off the high ones.

104
00:09:50,948 --> 00:09:52,983
"Good thing your sister bailed you out. "

105
00:09:54,851 --> 00:09:57,520
"Kit, why don't you get your sister
to teach you how to hit?"

106
00:09:58,455 --> 00:10:00,423
"Why can't you be beautiful
like your sister?"

107
00:10:01,157 --> 00:10:02,592
What idiot said that?

108
00:10:03,192 --> 00:10:04,193
No one.

109
00:10:04,694 --> 00:10:07,162
- But that's what they were thinking.
- No, it's not!

110
00:10:09,765 --> 00:10:11,667
You ever hear Dad
introduce us to people?

111
00:10:13,101 --> 00:10:14,803
"This is our daughter Dottie.

112
00:10:15,470 --> 00:10:18,339
This is our other daughter,
Dottie's sister.

113
00:10:19,941 --> 00:10:22,076
Should've just had you
and bought a dog.

114
00:10:23,210 --> 00:10:25,946
- Mitch Swaley likes you.
- He's one step up from dating pigs.

115
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:28,382
But an important step.

116
00:10:32,052 --> 00:10:33,820
- Why are you walking so fast?
- Why are you?

117
00:10:34,521 --> 00:10:37,457
- Because you are.
- Can't even let me walk faster than you?

118
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:49,801
Girls, you got chores to do.

119
00:10:54,505 --> 00:10:56,841
Don't run! You'll scare the chickens!

120
00:10:58,509 --> 00:11:00,477
I don't have time for these games.

121
00:11:01,845 --> 00:11:03,814
- Why are you running?
- You can go faster than that.

122
00:11:04,514 --> 00:11:05,682
Your legs are longer.

123
00:11:06,216 --> 00:11:07,584
- I win!
- Barely.

124
00:11:30,371 --> 00:11:31,039
Hey!

125
00:11:32,974 --> 00:11:33,975
Hey, yourself.

126
00:11:36,377 --> 00:11:37,244
Doesn't that hurt them?

127
00:11:39,146 --> 00:11:40,013
Doesn't seem to.

128
00:11:40,881 --> 00:11:42,983
It would bruise the hell out of me.

129
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:44,751
Who are you?

130
00:11:45,218 --> 00:11:46,920
I'm Ernie Capadino, baseball scout.

131
00:11:47,687 --> 00:11:50,556
I saw you playing today.
Not bad, not bad.

132
00:11:51,524 --> 00:11:53,292
Ever hear of Walter Harvey?
Harvey Bars?

133
00:11:53,993 --> 00:11:55,160
You know, the candy?

134
00:11:55,661 --> 00:11:57,996
Yeah, we feed them to the cows
when they're constipated.

135
00:11:58,830 --> 00:12:01,099
He's starting
a girls' baseball league...

136
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,169
...so we can make a buck
while the boys are overseas.

137
00:12:05,003 --> 00:12:05,937
Wanna play?

138
00:12:06,871 --> 00:12:10,871
Nice retort. Tryouts are in Chicago.
It's a real league, professional.

139
00:12:12,109 --> 00:12:13,677
Professional baseball?

140
00:12:15,245 --> 00:12:17,147
They'll pay you $75 a week.

141
00:12:18,615 --> 00:12:19,916
We only make $30 at the dairy.

142
00:12:20,450 --> 00:12:22,852
Then this would be more,
wouldn't it? Interested?

143
00:12:24,254 --> 00:12:26,355
Come on. $75 a week?

144
00:12:27,757 --> 00:12:29,525
Pull her leg. Mine are long enough.

145
00:12:30,192 --> 00:12:32,027
Look, your country needs you.

146
00:12:32,695 --> 00:12:35,297
You can not only play ball,
but you're kind of a dolly.

147
00:12:36,131 --> 00:12:38,466
Oh, now I get it.
Listen, mister.

148
00:12:39,501 --> 00:12:41,469
I'm a married woman.
My husband's overseas.

149
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:44,972
Oh, relax!
I'm talking lookie, no touchie.

150
00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:47,174
We want girls easy on the eye.

151
00:12:47,708 --> 00:12:50,044
I'll go. I'm ready now.
I gotta sign something?

152
00:12:50,844 --> 00:12:53,714
I don't want you! I want her!
The one who hit the ball!

153
00:12:54,614 --> 00:12:56,316
You can climb back under the cow.

154
00:12:57,217 --> 00:12:58,585
She's good. She's very good.

155
00:12:59,119 --> 00:13:01,521
She pitches. She didn't today,
because she did yesterday.

156
00:13:02,388 --> 00:13:04,423
Thanks for that special glimpse
into her life.

157
00:13:05,257 --> 00:13:06,058
I want you.

158
00:13:06,792 --> 00:13:08,227
You I saw, you I like.

159
00:13:08,861 --> 00:13:10,295
The train leaves for Chicago tomorrow.

160
00:13:11,763 --> 00:13:13,198
What do you say?
Are you in?

161
00:13:13,765 --> 00:13:14,432
No, thanks.

162
00:13:16,601 --> 00:13:17,735
"No, thanks"?

163
00:13:18,570 --> 00:13:19,937
Hey, no skin off my Ashtabula.

164
00:13:20,538 --> 00:13:22,707
If you wanna pluck cows,
that's your business.

165
00:13:23,441 --> 00:13:25,009
You know something? You're not nice.

166
00:13:26,543 --> 00:13:28,745
That one hurt. So long, milkmaids.

167
00:13:35,452 --> 00:13:36,452
No, wait!

168
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:40,356
Just watch me pitch. Dottie,
get your mitt! I'll throw him a few.

169
00:13:43,659 --> 00:13:44,760
Now look...

170
00:13:45,294 --> 00:13:48,163
...I know the goods when I see
the goods, and she's the goods.

171
00:13:49,765 --> 00:13:50,866
I'm sorry.

172
00:13:57,672 --> 00:13:59,373
Will you shut up?!

173
00:14:01,242 --> 00:14:02,476
You're a pitcher, huh?

174
00:14:07,614 --> 00:14:09,950
I'll tell you what.
If she comes, you can come too.

175
00:14:11,051 --> 00:14:13,186
If you stink, it only costs us
the train ticket.

176
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,555
Get these wild animals away from me!

177
00:14:16,222 --> 00:14:17,857
Haven't you ever heard of a leash?

178
00:14:22,161 --> 00:14:23,162
Come on, Dottie.

179
00:14:23,629 --> 00:14:26,298
You got the whole rest of your life
to hang around here.

180
00:14:27,232 --> 00:14:29,334
Never go anywhere. Never do anything.

181
00:14:30,568 --> 00:14:33,438
I'm married. I'm happy.
It's what I want. Don't confuse things.

182
00:14:39,410 --> 00:14:41,178
But can't you just have this first?

183
00:14:41,912 --> 00:14:45,482
Just so you can say you once
did something? Something special?

184
00:14:49,085 --> 00:14:50,086
Goodness sake, Kit!

185
00:14:50,753 --> 00:14:53,689
Keep your voice down.
Your father's listening to the radio.

186
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:57,092
Please, Dottie?

187
00:14:58,927 --> 00:15:00,429
I gotta get out of here.

188
00:15:01,930 --> 00:15:03,365
I'm nothing here.

189
00:15:14,008 --> 00:15:15,909
In the Pacific Northwest,
my territory...

190
00:15:16,677 --> 00:15:20,313
...we have increased sales 106%
in the last 12-month period.

191
00:15:21,481 --> 00:15:22,983
And this with a war on!

192
00:15:26,953 --> 00:15:30,022
You know, if I had your job,
I'd kill myself.

193
00:15:31,957 --> 00:15:34,360
Sit here. I'll see if I can
dig up a pistol.

194
00:15:36,528 --> 00:15:39,131
Every trip I take, I gotta sit
next to one of these guys.

195
00:15:40,031 --> 00:15:41,333
I'm just too friendly.

196
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:42,867
Hey, isn't that-?

197
00:15:46,971 --> 00:15:49,707
Well, I'll say one thing for them.
They can run.

198
00:15:50,975 --> 00:15:52,209
Mr. Capadino!

199
00:15:52,810 --> 00:15:53,811
I got her! Look!

200
00:15:55,279 --> 00:15:57,247
- Sir, your knee.
- Like it?

201
00:15:58,148 --> 00:15:59,516
Stop the train!

202
00:16:04,220 --> 00:16:05,655
Come on! Come on!

203
00:16:10,726 --> 00:16:11,827
Give me that bag!

204
00:16:25,006 --> 00:16:26,974
Did you promise the cows you'd write?

205
00:16:36,149 --> 00:16:37,784
When do we get to Chicago?

206
00:16:39,252 --> 00:16:41,721
We gotta make a stop.
Fort Collins, Colorado.

207
00:16:43,022 --> 00:16:44,590
Gotta look at another girl.

208
00:16:45,691 --> 00:16:47,126
Hope you're not jealous.

209
00:16:53,932 --> 00:16:54,599
I'm sorry.

210
00:16:54,999 --> 00:16:56,768
It's okay, honey. That was good form.

211
00:17:00,171 --> 00:17:01,172
Thattagirl!

212
00:17:01,839 --> 00:17:03,340
Good, honey. Good.

213
00:17:06,577 --> 00:17:07,311
Nice, nice.

214
00:17:07,711 --> 00:17:08,812
That's a rope, honey.

215
00:17:10,380 --> 00:17:11,815
Good girl. Good, good.

216
00:17:13,483 --> 00:17:14,350
Right, too high.

217
00:17:14,984 --> 00:17:16,686
She's got an eye like DiMaggio.

218
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:25,093
Okay, Marla.

219
00:17:25,594 --> 00:17:26,461
Now lefty.

220
00:17:41,241 --> 00:17:42,042
She's really good.

221
00:17:43,443 --> 00:17:44,244
She's your daughter?

222
00:17:48,214 --> 00:17:49,916
Her mom's dead.
It's just the two of us.

223
00:17:51,351 --> 00:17:53,886
Coach said if she was a boy,
she'd go to the state tournament.

224
00:17:54,720 --> 00:17:58,023
I said, "If she was a boy, I'd talk to
the Yankees instead of living here."

225
00:18:02,394 --> 00:18:04,096
That's enough.
You can bring her over.

226
00:18:04,763 --> 00:18:05,630
Okay, Marla.

227
00:18:06,231 --> 00:18:06,898
Come here.

228
00:18:07,298 --> 00:18:08,099
Boys!

229
00:18:08,533 --> 00:18:09,634
Hit the showers!

230
00:18:18,642 --> 00:18:20,010
Take off your hat, honey.

231
00:18:32,755 --> 00:18:33,989
We'll let you know.

232
00:18:35,758 --> 00:18:37,526
Daddy, I'm sorry.

233
00:18:38,227 --> 00:18:39,795
Let's go. We'll miss the train.

234
00:18:40,462 --> 00:18:42,030
Let's move, move, move!

235
00:18:44,566 --> 00:18:45,733
What's the matter?

236
00:18:47,135 --> 00:18:48,436
I can't use her.

237
00:18:48,970 --> 00:18:51,105
She's great. Why not?
What's the problem?

238
00:18:52,706 --> 00:18:54,541
You know General Omar Bradley?

239
00:18:55,709 --> 00:18:57,411
There's too strong a resemblance.

240
00:18:58,945 --> 00:19:00,981
You ain't taking her
because she ain't pretty?

241
00:19:01,748 --> 00:19:03,583
Well, look who just caught up!

242
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:05,685
All right. Come on, let's go.

243
00:19:07,887 --> 00:19:09,588
Pick those suitcases up! Come on!

244
00:19:10,322 --> 00:19:11,690
I'm not kidding. Move!

245
00:19:12,257 --> 00:19:13,826
- One foot in front of the other.
- Mister?

246
00:19:20,165 --> 00:19:22,834
I know my girl ain't so pretty
as these girls.

247
00:19:23,935 --> 00:19:25,303
But that's my fault.

248
00:19:26,103 --> 00:19:27,938
I raised her like I would a boy.

249
00:19:28,639 --> 00:19:29,807
I didn't know any better.

250
00:19:31,975 --> 00:19:33,744
She loves to play.

251
00:19:35,946 --> 00:19:38,548
Don't make my girl suffer
because I messed up raising her.

252
00:19:40,483 --> 00:19:41,417
Please?

253
00:19:45,521 --> 00:19:47,223
I wish you had a decent mitt.

254
00:19:48,490 --> 00:19:50,325
I think maybe I'd better not go.

