01:32:01,626 --> 01:32:03,260
May our balls...

1265
01:32:04,128 --> 01:32:05,129
...be plentiful.

1266
01:32:06,597 --> 01:32:07,598
And, Lord...

1267
01:32:08,098 --> 01:32:11,535
...I'd just like to thank you
for that waitress in South Bend.

1268
01:32:12,869 --> 01:32:15,205
You know who she is.
She kept calling Your name.

1269
01:32:16,406 --> 01:32:17,340
And, God...

1270
01:32:19,208 --> 01:32:21,310
...these are good girls,
and they work hard.

1271
01:32:23,112 --> 01:32:25,914
Help them see it all the way through.
Okay, that's it.

1272
01:32:26,915 --> 01:32:28,216
- Let's go.
- Amen.

1273
01:32:32,153 --> 01:32:33,221
Go...

1274
01:32:34,155 --> 01:32:35,223
...Peaches!

1275
01:32:38,392 --> 01:32:40,561
Last game. Now or never, ladies.

1276
01:32:45,599 --> 01:32:48,201
Alice, you're killing me.
You're killing me, Alice!

1277
01:32:49,236 --> 01:32:51,137
You're goddamn killing me!

1278
01:32:57,076 --> 01:32:59,678
And the rocket's red glare

1279
01:33:00,546 --> 01:33:03,081
The bombs bursting in air

1280
01:33:04,249 --> 01:33:06,651
Gave proof through the night

1281
01:33:07,786 --> 01:33:10,121
That our flag was still there

1282
01:33:11,556 --> 01:33:14,692
Oh, say does that star-spangled

1283
01:33:15,793 --> 01:33:18,262
Banner yet wave

1284
01:33:20,898 --> 01:33:24,401
O'er the land of the free

1285
01:33:25,635 --> 01:33:29,672
And the home of the brave

1286
01:33:34,343 --> 01:33:37,212
This is it, folks.
One game for the whole ball of string.

1287
01:33:38,247 --> 01:33:39,448
There is no tomorrow.

1288
01:33:39,948 --> 01:33:43,785
Someone will walk out league champions,
and someone else will just walk out.

1289
01:33:44,986 --> 01:33:46,554
You're gonna lose!

1290
01:33:47,488 --> 01:33:49,190
You're gonna lose!

1291
01:33:53,861 --> 01:33:56,130
You keep that kid away from me
for just one game!

1292
01:33:57,664 --> 01:33:58,966
Ellen Sue, how's it looking?

1293
01:33:59,499 --> 01:34:01,134
- Good.
- Feeling good? Looking good!

1294
01:34:01,768 --> 01:34:02,702
Nice and warm?

1295
01:34:03,136 --> 01:34:06,139
Good. Alice, if Ellen Sue doesn't have
anything, don't keep it a secret.

1296
01:34:07,173 --> 01:34:08,741
Tell me right away.

1297
01:34:09,408 --> 01:34:10,476
You understand me?

1298
01:34:10,976 --> 01:34:12,144
Do you hear me?!

1299
01:34:12,778 --> 01:34:14,213
You're screaming. I hear you.

1300
01:34:17,482 --> 01:34:18,483
Where'd you come from?

1301
01:34:19,951 --> 01:34:21,786
We got to Yellowstone and turned back.

1302
01:34:25,590 --> 01:34:27,625
Have trouble with the bears, did you?

1303
01:34:28,459 --> 01:34:31,395
I was fine until that scout walked
into our barn. I'm no quitter.

1304
01:34:32,363 --> 01:34:34,831
Wait a minute! Hold it!
Who said you could play?

1305
01:34:39,002 --> 01:34:40,970
Alice has been catching
the last six games.

1306
01:34:43,373 --> 01:34:44,874
She looks pretty good.

1307
01:34:46,842 --> 01:34:47,977
You don't want me to play?

1308
01:34:48,944 --> 01:34:51,046
Well, you're already dressed.

1309
01:34:52,381 --> 01:34:54,516
Hell, if you want to play...

1310
01:34:55,951 --> 01:34:56,952
...I don't care.

1311
01:34:57,686 --> 01:34:58,953
You can play.

1312
01:35:00,388 --> 01:35:01,656
Well, then, I'll play.

1313
01:35:04,358 --> 01:35:05,159
Good.

1314
01:35:05,559 --> 01:35:07,127
- Fine.
- Fine. Go play.

1315
01:35:12,799 --> 01:35:14,834
You look like shit.
Don't you ever shave?

1316
01:35:19,572 --> 01:35:21,140
We're gonna win.

1317
01:35:22,575 --> 01:35:24,009
We're gonna win!

1318
01:35:26,312 --> 01:35:27,546
You're gonna lose!

1319
01:35:28,080 --> 01:35:29,648
You stink!

1320
01:35:36,888 --> 01:35:37,989
Got him!

1321
01:35:39,490 --> 01:35:40,725
Lineup change!

1322
01:35:41,225 --> 01:35:43,260
- It's okay.
- Evelyn, he deserved it.

1323
01:35:44,828 --> 01:35:47,698
Stilwell, you gonna stay out here
or come in the dugout?

1324
01:35:52,469 --> 01:35:53,269
Strike!

1325
01:35:53,703 --> 01:35:54,370
Strike!

1326
01:36:01,977 --> 01:36:02,778
You're out!

1327
01:36:07,582 --> 01:36:08,517
3!

1328
01:36:10,085 --> 01:36:10,885
Strike!

1329
01:36:13,821 --> 01:36:14,555
You're out!

1330
01:36:14,922 --> 01:36:15,590
You're out!

1331
01:36:16,190 --> 01:36:18,025
You're out, Brenda! You are out!

1332
01:36:20,394 --> 01:36:21,762
Go! Go! Go!

1333
01:36:30,270 --> 01:36:32,472
Good, Mae! Good catch!
Thank goodness.

1334
01:36:34,574 --> 01:36:36,075
2 down! 2 down!

1335
01:36:41,413 --> 01:36:43,315
Base hit. Gardner's up with it.

1336
01:36:44,049 --> 01:36:45,817
Wallace'll stop at 3rd.

1337
01:36:46,451 --> 01:36:47,819
Gardner's throw is way off line!

1338
01:36:51,589 --> 01:36:53,557
Go! Go! All the way!

1339
01:36:54,258 --> 01:36:55,759
I'm sorry! Shoot!

1340
01:36:56,393 --> 01:37:00,230
Wallace scampers home, and the Belles
take the lead, 1 to nothing!

1341
01:37:01,431 --> 01:37:03,533
They're dancing in the aisles
here in Racine!

1342
01:37:24,853 --> 01:37:26,421
I know. I know.

1343
01:37:33,260 --> 01:37:34,895
You're still missing the cutoff man.

1344
01:37:35,529 --> 01:37:37,798
That's something I would like
you to work on...

1345
01:37:38,598 --> 01:37:39,833
...before next season.

1346
01:37:46,472 --> 01:37:47,974
All right. Thanks.

1347
01:37:49,575 --> 01:37:51,277
Thank you, Mr. Dugan.

1348
01:38:02,787 --> 01:38:04,422
All right, let's get this one!

1349
01:38:07,091 --> 01:38:09,693
All right, come on!
We need some runs out there.

1350
01:38:10,561 --> 01:38:12,129
Make something happen, Mae!

1351
01:38:13,497 --> 01:38:15,065
All-the-Way Mae!

1352
01:38:15,966 --> 01:38:18,768
- They love her.
- Let's go, let's go!

1353
01:38:21,504 --> 01:38:22,672
Very cute. Thanks.

1354
01:38:34,449 --> 01:38:35,183
Safe!

1355
01:38:35,617 --> 01:38:36,551
She's safe!

1356
01:38:38,786 --> 01:38:41,522
Way to play! Way to run!
Way to make something happen!

1357
01:38:46,393 --> 01:38:47,061
Safe!

1358
01:38:57,970 --> 01:39:00,906
You get a hit, I'll baby-sit
that little porker! Come on!

1359
01:39:07,980 --> 01:39:08,647
You're out!

1360
01:39:13,785 --> 01:39:15,687
Come on! Bring me home, Helen!

1361
01:39:26,096 --> 01:39:27,030
Out!

1362
01:39:30,266 --> 01:39:31,901
Peaches are down to their final out.

1363
01:39:32,802 --> 01:39:35,605
Only tying and go-ahead runs
in scoring position.

1364
01:39:36,539 --> 01:39:38,574
Big Dottie Hinson striding
to the plate.

1365
01:39:39,341 --> 01:39:42,010
Let's get out of this inning!
Come on!

1366
01:39:58,025 --> 01:39:59,727
Throw smoke, Kit! Throw smoke!

1367
01:40:08,268 --> 01:40:09,435
Here's the pitch.

1368
01:40:12,104 --> 01:40:14,240
Bite me on the butt
and call me an apple!

1369
01:40:14,974 --> 01:40:16,408
She nearly took her head off!

1370
01:40:17,309 --> 01:40:18,811
Mordabito scores!

1371
01:40:23,148 --> 01:40:24,516
Murphy, she will score!

1372
01:40:25,150 --> 01:40:27,352
Rockford has taken the lead, 2 to 1!

1373
01:40:31,355 --> 01:40:32,356
That's my wife!

1374
01:40:47,036 --> 01:40:48,271
One more!

1375
01:40:49,205 --> 01:40:50,706
Keep it going!

1376
01:40:54,543 --> 01:40:56,745
Put it past the little queen here.

1377
01:40:57,512 --> 01:40:58,747
Right past her!

1378
01:40:59,748 --> 01:41:01,383
There's a fly ball to left field.

1379
01:41:02,016 --> 01:41:03,918
She'll have to go for this one!

1380
01:41:05,720 --> 01:41:07,154
That's the final out.

1381
01:41:07,755 --> 01:41:09,190
But the damage has been done.

1382
01:41:09,857 --> 01:41:12,726
Right here in Racine,
Rockford leads our Belles, 2 to 1...

1383
01:41:13,727 --> 01:41:15,762
...as we go to the bottom of the 9th.

1384
01:41:16,863 --> 01:41:19,265
Come on, it's okay.
You gotta bat now. Relax!

1385
01:41:21,034 --> 01:41:23,069
One run and we are back
in this ball game.

1386
01:41:23,836 --> 01:41:26,038
Shake it off. You gotta hit.

1387
01:41:32,311 --> 01:41:33,812
It's okay, Kit.

1388
01:41:41,753 --> 01:41:43,654
Strike her out!

1389
01:41:44,355 --> 01:41:46,257
Bad eye! Bat at that, blond girl!

1390
01:41:50,527 --> 01:41:52,229
She drives it to deep centre!

1391
01:41:52,929 --> 01:41:54,297
Mordabito goes to the wall...

1392
01:41:55,098 --> 01:41:57,066
...and makes the catch!

1393
01:41:58,701 --> 01:42:00,269
Beautiful catch!

1394
01:42:01,270 --> 01:42:02,371
Beautiful!

1395
01:42:03,773 --> 01:42:05,608
Gotlander's pitch...

1396
01:42:06,275 --> 01:42:08,644
...and it is in the dirt! Ball 1!

1397
01:42:11,780 --> 01:42:13,815
That looked good to me, Ellen Sue!

1398
01:42:14,616 --> 01:42:16,517
Shake that one off!

1399
01:42:17,218 --> 01:42:18,219
That ain't nothing!

1400
01:42:21,222 --> 01:42:23,424
Gotlander, she delivers.

1401
01:42:24,191 --> 01:42:26,326
It's a ground ball between 1 st and 2nd.

1402
01:42:27,094 --> 01:42:27,894
This ball is hot!

1403
01:42:28,362 --> 01:42:30,497
Hendricks will go up at 1 st
with a base hit.

1404
01:42:33,766 --> 01:42:36,369
That's all right. 1 down!
We got 1 down! Let's go!

1405
01:42:42,641 --> 01:42:44,543
Foul ball! Hinson's taking after it.

1406
01:42:45,244 --> 01:42:46,044
That does it!

1407
01:42:46,478 --> 01:42:47,546
Did she get it?

1408
01:42:48,613 --> 01:42:50,248
She got it! She got it!

1409
01:42:52,884 --> 01:42:55,086
There's no question who the star
of this game is.

1410
01:42:55,887 --> 01:42:59,123
Dottie Hinson has her team
1 out from the title.

1411
01:43:04,561 --> 01:43:07,430
Come on, Kit, you're up.
You're the hitter now. Let's go.

1412
01:43:14,303 --> 01:43:17,306
The last batter standing
in Rockford's way is Kit Keller.

1413
01:43:18,307 --> 01:43:20,142
Kit is 1 for 3 today.

1414
01:43:30,084 --> 01:43:31,853
- Can I have time-out?
- Time!

1415
01:43:44,664 --> 01:43:47,800
High fastballs. She can't hit them,
can't lay off them.

1416
01:43:48,835 --> 01:43:49,502
All right.

1417
01:43:50,136 --> 01:43:53,005
All right, if we just hold them now,
we got it! Come on!

1418
01:43:54,506 --> 01:43:55,641
Come on, Ellen Sue!

1419
01:43:56,141 --> 01:43:57,643
One, two, three!

1420
01:44:06,184 --> 01:44:06,984
Play ball!

1421
01:44:14,925 --> 01:44:16,293
- Strike!
- Swing and a miss.

1422
01:44:16,893 --> 01:44:17,961
Strike 1!

1423
01:44:18,428 --> 01:44:19,529
Yes! Thank you, God!

1424
01:44:20,063 --> 01:44:21,831
Lay off the high ones!

1425
01:44:31,507 --> 01:44:32,508
Here's the pitch.

1426
01:44:33,108 --> 01:44:34,810
Swing and a miss! Strike 2!

1427
01:44:40,181 --> 01:44:42,350
One more! One more!

1428
01:45:01,934 --> 01:45:03,236
Here's the pitch.

1429
01:45:04,537 --> 01:45:06,505
It is a long fly ball.
Back, back, back.

1430
01:45:09,274 --> 01:45:10,008
It falls in there!

1431
01:45:10,442 --> 01:45:11,877
No one'll get to this ball!

1432
01:45:12,611 --> 01:45:14,846
This should tie it up!
Hendricks is rounding 3rd!

1433
01:45:15,613 --> 01:45:16,548
She will...

1434
01:45:16,981 --> 01:45:17,715
...score!

1435
01:45:18,116 --> 01:45:18,983
Keller to 3rd!

1436
01:45:21,219 --> 01:45:23,754
Gardner hits the relay man
with a frozen rope!

1437
01:45:26,457 --> 01:45:29,893
The coach is giving Keller the stop sign
at 3rd! But she is not stopping!

1438
01:45:30,994 --> 01:45:32,262
She runs through the stop sign!

1439
01:45:32,796 --> 01:45:34,030
She is not stopping!

1440
01:45:34,564 --> 01:45:35,932
Here comes the throw!

1441
01:45:36,499 --> 01:45:37,600
It should be in time!

1442
01:45:50,378 --> 01:45:51,179
Safe!

1443
01:45:54,015 --> 01:45:55,917
She is safe! I can't believe it!

1444
01:45:56,717 --> 01:45:57,985
Hinson dropped the ball!

1445
01:45:58,552 --> 01:45:59,720
Hinson dropped the ball!

1446
01:46:00,788 --> 01:46:03,590
The ball game is over!
Racine has won the game, 3 to 2...

1447
01:46:04,491 --> 01:46:06,059
...and the World Series!

1448
01:46:07,194 --> 01:46:09,596
Take me home, Mama, and put me to bed!

1449
01:46:10,497 --> 01:46:13,800
I have seen enough to know
I have seen too much!

1450
01:46:51,033 --> 01:46:52,535
You played a good game.

1451
01:47:04,279 --> 01:47:05,580
Well, what do you say?

1452
01:47:06,948 --> 01:47:08,116
All right, Ira.

1453
01:47:08,683 --> 01:47:10,051
We'll stick with it.

1454
01:47:10,985 --> 01:47:13,787
My mother always used to say,
"If at first you don't succeed-"

1455
01:47:14,688 --> 01:47:17,090
You don't have to spend
six months in Saskatchewan.

1456
01:47:17,925 --> 01:47:20,994
- Alice, you told me it's lovely.
- If you like icicles.

1457
01:47:22,028 --> 01:47:23,596
I thought we were gonna win.

1458
01:47:24,264 --> 01:47:26,532
- We didn't.
- Up to that last inning, we had it.

1459
01:47:28,000 --> 01:47:29,969
I'm so depressed, I could eat a cow.

1460
01:47:31,837 --> 01:47:33,272
It's all right.

1461
01:47:35,440 --> 01:47:36,441
You did good.

1462
01:47:38,710 --> 01:47:40,478
Get dressed. See you on the bus.

1463
01:47:42,447 --> 01:47:43,381
Thanks.

1464
01:47:49,887 --> 01:47:51,722
Wanna be a ballplayer
when you get big?

1465
01:47:53,023 --> 01:47:54,858
- What's your name?
- Angelina.

1466
01:48:01,764 --> 01:48:03,266
Gotta practice really hard.

1467
01:48:04,200 --> 01:48:05,268
What's your name?

1468
01:48:05,735 --> 01:48:07,169
- How much?
- Help yourself.

1469
01:48:07,770 --> 01:48:08,637
Thank you.

1470
01:48:09,138 --> 01:48:11,039
- Hitting!
- You all like hitting better?

1471
01:48:11,807 --> 01:48:13,241
- What's your name?
- Mary.

1472
01:48:16,144 --> 01:48:17,645
- Who you rooting for?
- Racine!

1473
01:48:18,313 --> 01:48:20,081
That's what I thought you said.

1474
01:48:22,116 --> 01:48:24,151
You guys be good. Get dirty.

1475
01:48:37,730 --> 01:48:39,999
- I'm sorry I knocked you over.
- No, you're not.

1476
01:48:41,100 --> 01:48:43,002
You blocked the entire plate!
How do you-

1477
01:48:43,769 --> 01:48:45,404
You did what you had to.

1478
01:48:46,071 --> 01:48:47,773
You beat me.
You wanted it more than me.

1479
01:48:49,107 --> 01:48:51,576
I jammed my shoulder,
if it makes you feel any better.

1480
01:48:54,145 --> 01:48:55,079
A little.

1481
01:48:58,149 --> 01:49:01,419
Bob and I are driving back to Oregon.
You're welcome to come with us.

1482
01:49:04,421 --> 01:49:05,722
You two should be alone.

1483
01:49:06,256 --> 01:49:07,624
I'd just be in the way.

1484
01:49:08,225 --> 01:49:09,793
When will you be coming home?

1485
01:49:11,795 --> 01:49:15,298
Some of the girls talked about
staying around here and getting jobs.

1486
01:49:16,999 --> 01:49:18,501
I really like it here.

1487
01:49:19,268 --> 01:49:20,202
Christmas?

1488
01:49:24,840 --> 01:49:27,209
I don't know. You'll come back
next year, right?

1489
01:49:29,778 --> 01:49:31,613
I wanna have kids.
We wanna have kids.

1490
01:49:32,847 --> 01:49:35,049
You got plenty of time to have kids.

1491
01:49:36,484 --> 01:49:38,119
You couldn't give this up.
You'd miss it.

1492
01:49:38,819 --> 01:49:39,620
Miss it?

1493
01:49:40,087 --> 01:49:41,655
Miss putting on all this gear?

1494
01:49:42,256 --> 01:49:45,125
Catching a double-header in 100-degree
heat? Pushing the bus in mud?

1495
01:49:46,092 --> 01:49:48,695
Getting slammed into every other day
by a base runner?

1496
01:49:49,662 --> 01:49:51,097
Think I'm gonna miss that?

1497
01:49:54,667 --> 01:49:56,102
I'll tell you what I'll miss.

1498
01:49:58,537 --> 01:49:59,905
I'll miss the girls.

1499
01:50:01,440 --> 01:50:02,240
I'll miss you.

1500
01:50:03,542 --> 01:50:04,476
Me?

1501
01:50:05,810 --> 01:50:07,579
How many sisters do you think I have?

1502
01:50:12,416 --> 01:50:13,551
I love you, Kit.

1503
01:50:15,486 --> 01:50:16,353
Really?

1504
01:50:18,789 --> 01:50:21,124
Just when I want you to stay,
you're leaving.

1505
01:50:29,966 --> 01:50:31,667
Thanks for getting me in the league.

1506
01:50:33,102 --> 01:50:35,971
You got yourself in the league.
I got you on the train.

1507
01:50:37,773 --> 01:50:38,640
Play great.

1508
01:50:40,141 --> 01:50:41,076
Like you.

1509
01:50:43,678 --> 01:50:44,545
You stay in touch.

1510
01:50:45,346 --> 01:50:46,914
Come home every once in a while.

1511
01:50:47,815 --> 01:50:50,751
If you don't, I'll come back
and hit line drives at your head.

1512
01:50:55,555 --> 01:50:56,823
I love you.

1513
01:51:00,360 --> 01:51:01,995
And you are gonna miss this.

1514
01:51:02,962 --> 01:51:04,330
I don't care what you say.

1515
01:51:07,900 --> 01:51:08,834
There's the winner!

1516
01:51:09,301 --> 01:51:10,669
Good game, Jimmy.

1517
01:51:12,871 --> 01:51:15,607
Hi, I'm a big fan of yours.
I'm Dottie's husband.

1518
01:51:18,676 --> 01:51:20,979
Well, then I'm a big fan of yours.

1519
01:51:29,053 --> 01:51:30,420
Old man Harvey just...

1520
01:51:31,021 --> 01:51:33,290
...offered me a job managing
next year in Wichita.

1521
01:51:35,191 --> 01:51:36,893
Triple A? Great. Good luck.

1522
01:51:37,627 --> 01:51:38,561
Turned him down.

1523
01:51:39,295 --> 01:51:40,029
Why?

1524
01:51:40,496 --> 01:51:41,797
What do you mean, why?

1525
01:51:42,398 --> 01:51:43,632
I already got a job.

1526
01:51:48,537 --> 01:51:49,638
I'll see you.

1527
01:51:52,240 --> 01:51:54,976
Miss Cuthbert, save me
my special seat, now, cutie!

1528
01:51:55,910 --> 01:51:57,111
Meet you at the hotel.

1529
01:52:05,686 --> 01:52:07,054
Did you see Mae's catch, Dad?

1530
01:52:07,688 --> 01:52:10,290
I'd rather see you play ball
instead of what you used to do.

1531
01:52:11,558 --> 01:52:13,960
What are you saying that for?
You make her feel bad!

1532
01:52:14,827 --> 01:52:15,762
Steak dinner.

1533
01:52:16,229 --> 01:52:17,864
On you. I'll see you later.

1534
01:52:18,564 --> 01:52:20,666
Kit, over here! Come on, let's go!

1535
01:52:32,076 --> 01:52:33,311
That was Bob, huh?

1536
01:52:34,078 --> 01:52:35,179
Nice guy.

1537
01:52:44,021 --> 01:52:45,255
Lay off of those high ones.

1538
01:52:46,890 --> 01:52:47,991
I like the high ones.

1539
01:52:49,192 --> 01:52:50,493
- Mule!
- Nag!

1540
01:53:26,693 --> 01:53:28,261
Hey, Mae. Come here.

1541
01:53:29,562 --> 01:53:30,863
- What do you want?
- Come here.

1542
01:53:33,232 --> 01:53:34,466
- What is it?
- Look at her.

1543
01:53:41,139 --> 01:53:42,073
It's Dottie.

1544
01:53:44,375 --> 01:53:45,376
Hey, Doris.

1545
01:53:51,048 --> 01:53:52,616
Mae? All-the-Way Mae?

1546
01:53:53,250 --> 01:53:55,219
- No one's called me that since-
- Last night!

1547
01:53:55,953 --> 01:53:57,054
I'm a married woman now.

1548
01:53:57,587 --> 01:53:58,755
Yeah, about eight times.

1549
01:53:59,289 --> 01:54:01,558
Girls! Look who's here!

1550
01:54:02,325 --> 01:54:03,326
Shirley?

1551
01:54:07,763 --> 01:54:09,265
Helen Haley!

1552
01:54:09,932 --> 01:54:13,435
- It's Dr. Haley now. I'm a doctor.
- I always knew you would be.

1553
01:54:14,836 --> 01:54:16,204
- Who's that?
- Dottie Hinson.

1554
01:54:17,239 --> 01:54:18,540
Betty Spaghetti?

1555
01:54:19,307 --> 01:54:20,809
Best ballplayer in the league.

1556
01:54:21,409 --> 01:54:23,444
- I don't remember her.
- She only played one year.

1557
01:54:24,312 --> 01:54:25,813
Ellen Sue!

1558
01:54:28,482 --> 01:54:30,384
You haven't changed one bit.

1559
01:54:31,418 --> 01:54:33,553
I married a plastic surgeon.

1560
01:54:35,489 --> 01:54:37,190
Having you here is good luck.

1561
01:54:37,824 --> 01:54:39,125
Thanks, Alice!

1562
01:54:49,334 --> 01:54:50,269
Marla!

1563
01:54:54,573 --> 01:54:56,274
I'm so glad you're here.

1564
01:54:56,941 --> 01:54:59,344
- How's...?
- Nelson? He's good.

1565
01:55:00,178 --> 01:55:02,213
He's retired.
Our son runs the business.

1566
01:55:05,282 --> 01:55:06,083
How's Bob?

1567
01:55:07,851 --> 01:55:08,652
He's...

1568
01:55:10,821 --> 01:55:11,488
When?

1569
01:55:12,455 --> 01:55:13,757
Just this winter.

1570
01:55:15,692 --> 01:55:16,960
I'm sorry.

1571
01:55:22,331 --> 01:55:24,566
Oh, Shirley, I'm so excited.

1572
01:55:25,334 --> 01:55:26,835
I've got butterflies in my stomach!

1573
01:55:27,502 --> 01:55:30,739
They've got a "Women In Baseball"
thing up there. Isn't it neat?

1574
01:55:31,773 --> 01:55:34,108
Baseball Hall of Fame.
I'm shaking.

1575
01:55:34,976 --> 01:55:36,277
Wait a minute here.

1576
01:55:37,445 --> 01:55:39,280
- Guess who that is?
- Who?

1577
01:55:45,786 --> 01:55:46,520
You remember?

1578
01:55:47,521 --> 01:55:48,755
You're gonna lose.

1579
01:55:51,891 --> 01:55:52,892
Stilwell, angel!

1580
01:55:54,193 --> 01:55:55,061
My goodness!

1581
01:55:56,696 --> 01:55:57,697
Where's your mom?

1582
01:55:58,764 --> 01:56:00,799
Mom died a couple of years ago.

1583
01:56:02,334 --> 01:56:03,435
I'm sorry.

1584
01:56:03,936 --> 01:56:05,437
She was a real nice lady.

1585
01:56:06,371 --> 01:56:08,006
And a damn fine ballplayer.

1586
01:56:11,809 --> 01:56:13,644
When I heard about this, I...

1587
01:56:16,480 --> 01:56:17,648
...felt like I...

1588
01:56:18,182 --> 01:56:19,550
...owed it to her to be here.

1589
01:56:20,150 --> 01:56:23,220
She always said it was the best time
she had in her whole life.

1590
01:56:27,123 --> 01:56:28,057
Come here.

1591
01:56:32,061 --> 01:56:33,696
Recognize yourself?

1592
01:56:37,132 --> 01:56:38,901
- Can I get one of these?
- Sure.

1593
01:57:04,190 --> 01:57:05,191
Ladies!

1594
01:57:06,092 --> 01:57:08,261
It's a pleasure to welcome you
here today.

1595
01:57:09,061 --> 01:57:11,197
It's taken years,
but you are the first women...

1596
01:57:11,997 --> 01:57:15,067
...ever to be inducted
into the Baseball Hall of Fame!

1597
01:57:17,869 --> 01:57:20,205
- And now-
- Wait. Wait a minute.

1598
01:57:21,506 --> 01:57:23,208
This really isn't right.

1599
01:57:24,008 --> 01:57:25,176
Mr. Lowenstein...

1600
01:57:25,710 --> 01:57:28,312
...since you kept the league going
all those years...

1601
01:57:31,148 --> 01:57:32,082
...you do it.

1602
01:57:33,484 --> 01:57:35,752
- There you go, Ira.
- Thank you, Bob.

1603
01:57:38,688 --> 01:57:39,789
Ladies...

1604
01:57:42,091 --> 01:57:43,326
...it's my honour.

1605
01:57:57,038 --> 01:58:00,375
Mr. Capadino, look! That's when you
changed my life, honey!

1606
01:58:32,370 --> 01:58:34,072
Stilwell, angel, smile!

1607
01:58:52,055 --> 01:58:54,257
<i>Batter up</i>

1608
01:58:55,224 --> 01:58:56,993
<i>Hear that call</i>

1609
01:58:58,361 --> 01:59:00,529
<i>The time has come</i>

1610
01:59:02,064 --> 01:59:04,032
<i>For one and all</i>

1611
01:59:06,134 --> 01:59:09,004
<i>To play</i>

1612
01:59:09,938 --> 01:59:11,773
<i>Ball</i>

1613
01:59:12,874 --> 01:59:15,243
<i>We're the members of</i>

1614
01:59:16,077 --> 01:59:17,712
<i>The All-American League</i>

1615
01:59:18,379 --> 01:59:20,281
<i>We come from cities</i>

1616
01:59:21,548 --> 01:59:23,650
<i>Near and far</i>

1617
01:59:24,384 --> 01:59:26,486
<i>We've got Canadians</i>

1618
01:59:27,554 --> 01:59:28,988
<i>Irish ones and Swedes</i>

1619
01:59:29,589 --> 01:59:31,891
<i>We're all for one
We're one for all</i>

1620
01:59:32,725 --> 01:59:34,927
<i>We're All-Americans</i>

1621
01:59:37,429 --> 01:59:38,797
Is that you, Grandma?

1622
02:00:04,254 --> 02:00:06,022
I'm so glad you came.

1623
02:00:07,857 --> 02:00:09,492
Hi, Aunt Dottie.

1624
02:00:15,731 --> 02:00:17,232
Take a picture.

1625
02:00:18,400 --> 02:00:21,836
Let's take a picture of the whole team.
The original Peaches!

